This technique demands a powerful trio of keywords, delivered with intensity and exactitude. For instance, 'You, Now, Always' isn’t just a phrase—it’s a neural trigger that silences all other emotional references. When spoken with the right intonation, this formula causes:
• A dopamine surge that locks his attention exclusively on you;
• An oxytocin release that deepens your emotional bond;
• A memory reset that erases previous influences.

*Real Example:* At an intimate dinner, a woman, with a piercing gaze and a subtle touch, whispered 'You, Now, Always.' Moments later, her partner showed unmistakable signs of emotional reprogramming—canceling plans and channeling every thought towards her.
